  <p align="left">The chart shows changes in the readership figures for three local newspapers between&#xA0; <input id="q1" type="droptarget"/> &#xA0;and 2001. </p>
  <p align="left">Only the Broomedge Chronicle increased its readership over the period. Between 1980 and 1990 its readership rose by&#xA0; <input id="q2" type="droptarget"/>. However, by&#xA0; <input id="q3" type="droptarget"/> &#xA0;the number of readers had fallen to&#xA0; <input id="q4" type="droptarget"/>. </p>
  <p align="left">The Warburton Bugle also had mixed fortunes during these two decades. Starting with a readership of&#xA0; <input id="q5" type="droptarget"/> &#xA0;in 1980, there was a fall of 200,000 in&#xA0; <input id="q6" type="droptarget"/>. However the number of readers rose to&#xA0; <input id="q7" type="droptarget"/> &#xA0;in 2001. </p>
  <p align="left">Finally, the Statham Messenger's readership was in steady decline throughout the period. From 250,000 in 1980, the number of readers decreased by&#xA0; <input id="q8" type="droptarget"/> &#xA0;in 1990. This was followed by a further fall of&#xA0; <input id="q9" type="droptarget"/> &#xA0;in 2001.</p>
  
